Interface PhysicalDrone

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PhysicalDroneTello

    public interface PhysicalDrone
    Interface containing a selection of possible drone flight commands mostly independent of drone manufacturer 09/30/2019 v1.0
    Author:
    MasterControlProgram

        Requests drone fly along a curve in three dimensions defined by two points Starts with current location as origin flying through first point and ending at second point
        Parameters:
        x1 - integer value of mid point along the x axis with lower bound up and upper bound of possible distance set by SDK
        y1 - integer value of mid point along the y axis with lower bound up and upper bound of possible distance set by SDK
        z1 - integer value of mid point along the z axis with lower bound up and upper bound of possible distance set by SDK
        x2 - integer value of end point along the x axis with lower bound up and upper bound of possible distance set by SDK
        y2 - integer value of end point along the y axis with lower bound up and upper bound of possible distance set by SDK
        z2 - integer value of end point along the z axis with lower bound up and upper bound of possible distance set by SDK
        speed - integer value setting some distance travelled per some unit time determined by SDK

      • hoverInPlace

        void hoverInPlace(int seconds)
           throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Requests the drone hover at current altitude for a set number of seconds depending on the safety features of the drone steps must be taken to prevent emergency landings and communication loss
        Parameters:
        seconds - number of seconds to hover in place
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - uses timer classes and may be interruptable
